         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">7/10/85 ¶  ¶ Your excellent son, ¶  dear Sir Joseph, was introduced by me to H. Exc. the Governor, ¶  also to some other influential people. My own idea is, that the young Gentleman should endeavour, ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.10.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-1890, second and third un-numbered folios after folio f. 159.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">7/10/85</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your excellent son,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Brian Hooker. See also M to J. Hooker, 2 October 1885.</p>
               </note> dear Sir Joseph, was introduced by me to H. Exc. the Governor,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir Henry Loch.</p>
               </note> also to some other influential people. My own idea is, that the young Gentleman should endeavour, to get as a Volunteer on some pastoral estate, best near some mining District, so that he can keep up his researches on mining resources as a byework.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In Australia the best road to fortune is in rearing sheep; far inland and on places with <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">permanent</hi>
               </seg> water prosperity in pastoral pursuits is certain, while at best in mining affairs it is an <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">uncertainty</hi>
               </seg>. One year is sufficient, to gain all the experience needed; it would cost almost nothing, and surely your son has some youthful friends in Britain with some few hundred £ each, to join him after the year on a new pastoral establishment of their own, where for some time they could do much of their work themselves.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I had a kind letter from Sir John Lubbock, in acknowledgement of Mrs Lewellens <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>-leaves.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found. See G. Lewellen to M, 29 May 1885, and M to J. Hooker, 30 May 1885 and notes thereto.</p>
               </note> He sent her and also me copies of his important essay on leaves.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Lubbock (1885).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall write soon to the President of the Linneans<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir John Lubbock was President of the Linnean Society of London from 1881 to 1886 (Gage &amp; Stearn (1988), p. 219).</p>
               </note> and Mrs L. whe[re] [I] [can] send more leaves<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The text treated as a postscript is on a separate undated sheet bound between this letter and f. 160.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
